Rating: 0
Just made this with some changes & love it. I needed to use up 1 yam & 1 russet, which together weighed half the total amount called for -- so I made half the recipe in an 8"x8" pan. No fresh herbs on hand, so used dried herbes de Provence -- no cream, so used undiluted evaporated milk -- halved the butter to avoid greasiness -- no Gruyere or Gouda on hand & I didn't think that Cheddar or Parmesan sounded good with yams, so used bleu -- halved the salt due to the strong cheese. It baked fine in the time given by the recipe (that may be because I used a mandolin to be sure the yam & potato were sliced thin enough). I didn't soak the potatoes, just kept the slices wrapped in damp towels until they were used (that may be why it didn't come out watery -- I did let it stand 10 minutes per directions). The bleu cheese taste is strong, as are the dried herbs, but I like that -- if I were serving others, I'd probably tone both of those down a little. Excellent recipe, especially good for a crowd. Thanks!

