after reading some of the other reviews it dawned on me that i should probably post that i always do this recipe the day before all the way through. i leave it in the fridge, covered, and leave the tinfoil on it when i pop it in the oven the next day. i cook it at about 350-400 (depending on what else i happen to have in the oven) for about 20-30 mins just until it is heated through. i have never had an issue with it being to watery but that's probably because it has so much time to sit after it's taken out of the oven the first time. i also switch the whipping cream for half and half and reduce the amount of butter just to lighten it up a little. works out perfectly every time and i love that it can be done ahead so i have one less thing to worry about when doing a big feast! love it!!

