I followed the recipe to a T. I discovered, like few others, that the cooking time is not correct. It requires 1hr in the oven wrapped in foil and another 40 minutes without the foil, to allow the liquid to be fully absorbed. This recipe requires more salt than called for, double the quantity required for sure, same with the black pepper. The quantity of the butter, on the other hand, should be cut by half at the very least otherwise the recipe is too greasy. Next time (because there will definitely be a next time), I will use half milk and half whipping cream, and I am sure with these alterations, my gratin will be perfect. Very tasty crowd pleaser indeed.

