Rating: 4
This was fantastic. I made it for the first time for a dinner party this weekend. I followed the recipe exactly except I added some celery root and the grocery store was out of Italian parsley so I didn't put any in. It was a little time consuming to cut all the potatoes by hand. I made sure to make the slices pretty thin, which I think is necessary to make sure everything comes out soft. I cooked an extra 15 or 20 minutes longer than the recipe called for so that the liquid would be absorbed. Everyone at the dinner party loved it and asked for the recipe. Even my husband said a couple of times that it was really good and he rarely is effusive about food. I'm making it again for another party this weekend for sure.

