Rating: 4
My more delicate variation was a big hit at Thanksgiving: I substituted all yams for the Yukon Golds, sliced very thin on the mandoline; used only rosemary and thyme; and swapped in 1 cup chopped marcona almonds with rosemary instead of the cheese. The nuts go on midway through the baking when you remove the foil. I also steeped the herbs in the cream along with the garlic -- by mistake from bad recipe reading, but it came out great. It needed a bit more cream without the cheese.

