Rating: 4
This was fabulously rich and satisfying. I made it with a turkey meatloaf which baked along side. This was a bit tedious to prepare. Use a sharp knife to get a consistent cut. I didn't use the Cuisinart because I didn't trust it to make the circles that I wanted. It was a nice challenge to cut the potatoes evenly. I was not true to the Scarborough Fair theme of parsley, sage, rosemary and thyme as I substitute chives which I had on hand. I liked the onion flavor. The fresh herbs stood out and made the taste superbly complex. The finished product was beautiful, browned, soft and crunchy.